Tier I AgDrift Curve Comparisons

C. Kuan

Thursday, March 03, 2016

Tier I Aerial

  • Preset Model Runs with 4 Drop Size Classes
  • Very Fine to Fine
  • Fine to Medium
  • Medium to Coarse
  • Coarse to Very Coarse

Tier I Ground

  • Field data curve fits with 2 Drop Size Classes at 2 Boom Heights (Low and High)
  • Very Fine to Fine - Low and High
  • Fine to Medium Coarse - Low and High

Low Boom

D(x) = c/(1+ax)^b where D(x) represents deposition at x downwind distance (ft), and a (ft^-1), b, and c are curve-fitting parameters.

High Boom

D(x) = (c/(1+ax)^b) * (1+A exp(-Bx)) where D(x) represents deposition at x downwind distance (ft), and a (ft^-1), b, and c are curve-fitting parameters. The exponential expression is only for x downwind distance > 25 ft.

Tier I Airblast

  • Field Data Curve Fit with 5 orchard types
  • Orchard
  • Vineyard
  • Normal
  • Dense
  • Sparse

“Inside vs. Outside” refers to whether the treatment was applied inside or outside the rows of trees in the field study

D(x) = c/(1+ax)^b where D(x) represents deposition at x downwind distance (ft), and a (ft^-1), b, and c are curve-fitting parameters.
